ON Sunday, July 10, 2020, friends and families gathered to celebrate veteran and award-winning actor Olu Jacobs as he turned 80. At the invitation of Ajoke Silva and the couple’s two sons, Olu Jacobs turned 80 to the delight, merriment, and admiration of family, friends, Nollywood practitioners, and fans all over the world.   One year after viral burial Obi Cubana eulogises mom     Fela, Keith Richards inspired my career – Highlife Soes     There’s still hope for Nigeria – Davido   The occasion was held at the Glover Memorial Hall, Lagos Island, which was the perfect backdrop for a man whose entire career has been dedicated to enhancing the arts and promoting culture. Silva was all smiles as she received guests and led the pace of the celebrations, that had Mo Abudu, Soni, Betty Irabor, Richard Mofe-Damijo, Ego Boyo, Ayo Sobowale, Taiwo Ajai-Lycett, Patience Ozokwo, Kunle Afolayan, Emeka Rollas, Ngozi Nwosu, Victor Osuagwu, and a host of others. Ajoke Silva also saw to the cutting of the cake before giving an emotional vote of thanks. The event also included a documentary by famed filmmaker Femi Odugbemi on the life of the thespian as well as a stage play by Lufodo productions.